Malicious Code and Software Supply Chain Security including usage of open source software:

        - Vulnerabilities in applications - web, mobile, low-code-no-code, etc.
                - SQL / LDAP / OS injection
                - XSS
                - CSRF
                - SSRF
                - broken authorisation
                - session hijacking
                - etc
        - secure coding to ensure vulnerabilities do not materialise:
                - parametrisation of queries
                - input data validation
                - data typing
                - scheme verification
                - content security policy
                - HTTP header hardening
                - etc
        - secure deserialization
        - Subdomain takeover
        - Dependency management (SCA tools like OWASP Dependency-Check)             
        - Code signing and verification
        - Open source software and licensing

References:
1. https://owasp.org/www-project-secure-coding-practices-quick-reference-guide/stable-en/01-introduction/05-introduction


